      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLASSIC LASS (1) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 318m at this track, taking a Maiden in a handy 18.34. Should be in this for a long way. NAVY DAVIES (4) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 0.8 lengths at Temora in a handy 18.67 beating Irinka Alana. Awkwardly drawn but goes well at this distance. Must be included in calculations. RED ROCK LOTUS (5) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (20.23) last time in a Grade 5 at Gunnedah. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Got the money at her only try from this box. In the mix. MOLLY KEEPING (2) is right in the mix.",
